By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC,$
\[\cos A = \frac{7^2 + 9^2 - 8^2}{2 \cdot 7 \cdot 9} = \frac{11}{21}.\]Then
\[\sin A = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 A} = \frac{8 \sqrt{5}}{21},\]so
\begin{align*}
\tan \angle AQP &= \frac{PY}{QY} \\
&= \frac{AP \sin A}{AQ - AY} \\
&= \frac{AP \sin A}{AQ - AP \cos A} \\
