\[\cos C = \frac{8^2 + 9^2 - 7^2}{2 \cdot 8 \cdot 9} = \frac{2}{3}.\]Then
\[\sin C = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 C} = \frac{\sqrt{5}}{3}.\]Since $CR = CS,$
\begin{align*}
