&= \frac{\sin \frac{C}{2}}{1 - \cos \frac{C}{2}} \\
&= \frac{\frac{\sqrt{5}}{3}}{1 - \frac{2}{3}} \\
&= \sqrt{5}.
\end{align*}Finally,
